SIMPLE: lurid
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Lurid
<hw>Lu"rid</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>luridus</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Pale yellow; ghastly pale;
wan; gloomy; dismal.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Fierce o'er their beauty blazed the <qex>lurid</qex> flame.</q>
<rj><qau>Thomson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Wrapped in drifts of <qex>lurid</qex> smoke⟦br⟧
On the misty river tide.</q> <rj><qau>Tennyson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Having a brown color tinged with
red, as of flame seen through smoke.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Of a color tinged with purple,
yellow, and gray.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>Vivid, sensational, or shocking; graphic or
melodramatic; <as>as, the <ex>lurid</ex> details of a
murder</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Lurk</ent>⟦br⟧
